                        @{b}@{u}Location for the subway@{ub}@{uu}


Landscape-file(s) : Subway.dat

Needed tool(s)    : Text Editor    (GoldED, CygnusED, etc...)
                    Paint Program  (DPaint, PPaint, Brilliance, etc...)


The file: @{b}Subway.dat@{ub} contain the @{" coordinates " Link Coordinates} of the subway and
the location to jump to. This file is @{b}not@{ub} required to play the
game. When this file is left out the computer will completely ignore
the subway.

The first four numbers represent the area of the subway. The other
numbers are coordinates of places where you will jump to when you use
the subway. You must be able to jump to three locations. These should
be near another subway. The list should end with @{b}999@{ub}.


Example:

   entrance of subway:     where we will jump to:
                           location 1   location 2   location 3
     x1  y1  x2  y2          x1  y1       x1  y1       x1  y1
   -------------------------------------------------------------
      2 511  17 501 538 305 538 313 538 321   
    534 308 549 298   5 511   5 503   5 495
      .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .
      .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .
      .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .
    999
@EndNode

